title: Nicaragua frees two detained Catholic bishops and 15 priests
description: The most prominent of the detainees is Bishop Rolando Álvarez, 58, an outspoken critic of President Daniel Ortega who was locked up for more than a year.

title: After attempts to meddle in Taiwan’s elections fail, China takes stock
description: China issued angry statements and launched warships after Taiwan elected Lai Ching-te, whom Beijing views as a dangerous separatist. But will it go further?

title: Grief and vengeance: 100 days of war in Israel, Gaza and the West Bank
description: There is no end in sight in the war that started on Oct. 7. leaving people with a sense of desperation and despair.

title: Volcanic eruption threatens Icelandic town with lava flows
description: A volcano erupted in southwestern Iceland following a series of earthquakes, threatening the town of Grindavik with lava flows for the second time in a month.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: ‘Nobody will stop us,’ Netanyahu vows, marking 100 days of war
description: The Israeli prime minister said the fighting will not end until Hamas has been eliminated, while dismissing the genocide allegations Israel faces at the World Court.

title: Two Russian fathers backed army conscription. Only one son came home.
description: Russia said it wouldn’t send young conscripts to Ukraine. But the experiences of two young men show how eager the military is to ship them off to war.

title: Denmark remakes royal tradition with a new king — but no crown
description: Crown Prince Frederik will become king on Sunday in a simple ceremony devoid of the pomp and pageantry associated with other monarchs.

title: Jacinda Ardern, New Zealand’s former leader, marries after pandemic delay
description: Ardern, who canceled her wedding plans in 2022 during an omicron wave, said when she resigned last year that getting married was one of her goals after politics.
